overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The
  agent first conducted a thorough analysis of the existing codebase to identify
  discrepancies and missing features. Based on this review, a detailed plan was
  formulated and subsequently executed. Key implementations included adding a
  1-10 severity scale for tiredness with associated safety warnings,
  implementing detection and tailored recommendations for complex sleep
  disorders such as COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and integrating
  external resource links within the report. The agent also enhanced the
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring with weighted calculations,
  expanded the CSV export functionality to include all questionnaire data, and
  introduced new questions for pain severity and chronic fatigue screening. The
  process involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI components, and
  report generation logic across the application.
